特朗普打破先例，在就职总统后几小时内就向[[联邦选举委员会|联邦选举委员会]]（FEC）提交了竞选连任总统的材料，表达了自己参选连任的意愿。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.washingtonexaminer.com/trump-hints-at-re-election-bid-vowing-eight-years-of-great-things/article/2612632|title=Trump hints at re-election bid, vowing 'eight years' of 'great things'|last=Westwood|first=Sarah|work=Washington Examiner|date=2017-01-22|accessdate=2017-02-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170816152829/http://www.washingtonexaminer.com/trump-hints-at-re-election-bid-vowing-eight-years-of-great-things/article/2612632|archive-date=2017-08-16|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://docquery.fec.gov/cgi-bin/fecimg?_201701209041436569+0|title=PAGE BY PAGE REPORT DISPLAY FOR 201701209041436569 (Page 1 of 1)|publisher=Federal Election Commission|date=2017-01-20|accessdate=2017-02-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170222000306/http://docquery.fec.gov/cgi-bin/fecimg?_201701209041436569+0|archive-date=2017-02-22|dead-url=no}}</ref>这使得他的2016年选举委员会转变为2020年连任委员会。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.azfamily.com/story/34380443/trump-breaks-precedent-files-on-first-day-as-candidate-for-re-election|title=Trump breaks precedent, files as candidate for re-election on first day|work=Azfamily.com|date=2017-01-31|accessdate=2017-02-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170130223626/http://www.azfamily.com/story/34380443/trump-breaks-precedent-files-on-first-day-as-candidate-for-re-election|archive-date=2017-01-30|dead-url=yes}}</ref>特朗普在上任不到一个月时，就于2017年2月18日以在[[墨爾本_(佛羅里達州)|佛罗里达州墨尔本]]的一场竞选集会上正式开启了他的2020年竞选活动。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2017/02/trump-kicks-off-his-2020-reelection-campaign-on-saturday/516909/|title=Trump Kicks Off His 2020 Reelection Campaign on Saturday|last=Graham|first=David A.|work=The Atlantic|date=2017-02-15|accessdate=2017-02-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170219013437/https://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2017/02/trump-kicks-off-his-2020-reelection-campaign-on-saturday/516909/|archive-date=2017-02-19|dead-url=no}}</ref>2017年2月1日，他的竞选活动已经筹集到超过700万美元的资金。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/post-politics/wp/2017/01/31/president-trump-has-already-socked-away-more-than-7-million-for-his-2020-reelection/|title=Trump already has socked away more than $7 million for his 2020 reelection|website=Washington Post|accessdate=2017-02-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170215191929/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/post-politics/wp/2017/01/31/president-trump-has-already-socked-away-more-than-7-million-for-his-2020-reelection/|archive-date=2017-02-15|dead-url=no}}</ref>在任期前两年，特朗普的连任委员会就已筹集了6750万美元，使特朗普的竞选委员会在2019年初时手头就已有1930万美元的现金。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Donald Trump’s campaign cash machine: big, brawny and burning money|url=https://publicintegrity.org/politics/donald-trump-money-campaign-2020/|accessdate=2020-12-14|work=Center for Public Integrity|language=en-us|archive-date=2020-11-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201126190844/https://publicintegrity.org/politics/donald-trump-money-campaign-2020/|dead-url=no}}</ref>从2019年初到2020年7月，特朗普竞选团队和共和党为选举筹集了11亿美元，但他们很快就使用了其中的8亿美元，导致特朗普丧失了对[[民主党_(美国)|民主党]]提名人、前副总统[[乔·拜登|拜登]]的巨大竞选资金优势。<ref>{{Cite news|title=How Trump’s Billion-Dollar Campaign Lost Its Cash Advantage|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/09/07/us/politics/trump-election-campaign-fundraising.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2020-09-07|accessdate=2020-12-14|issn=0362-4331|language=en-US|first=Shane|last=Goldmacher|first2=Maggie|last2=Haberman|archive-date=2020-10-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201028131952/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/09/07/us/politics/trump-election-campaign-fundraising.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>竞选活动的资金紧缩迫使特朗普的广告支出骤减。<ref>{{Cite news|title=Trump Campaign Slashes Ad Spending in Key States in Cash Crunch|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-09-14/trump-campaign-slashes-ad-spending-in-key-states-in-cash-crunch|newspaper=Bloomberg.com|date=2020-09-14|accessdate=2020-12-14|language=en|archive-date=2021-01-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210108053251/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-09-14/trump-campaign-slashes-ad-spending-in-key-states-in-cash-crunch|dead-url=no}}</ref>特朗普竞选广告关注的重点是犯罪问题，声称如果他的对手拜登赢得总统职位，大城市将陷入无法无天的境地。<ref>{{Cite news|title=As Trump Pushes Into Portland, His Campaign Ads Turn Darker|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/07/21/us/politics/trump-portland-federal-agents.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2020-07-21|accessdate=2021-04-07|issn=0362-4331|language=en-US|first=Maggie|last=Haberman|first2=Nick|last2=Corasaniti|first3=Annie|last3=Karni|archive-date=2020-07-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200724032846/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/07/21/us/politics/trump-portland-federal-agents.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

自2020年春季，特朗普开始对本次选举提出质疑，在没有公开证据的前提下声称大选或将被“操纵”<ref>{{Cite web|title=Trump sees a ‘rigged election’ ahead. Democrats see a constitutional crisis in the making.|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2020/05/25/donald-trump-rigged-election-talk-fears-274477|accessdate=2020-12-14|work=POLITICO|language=en|archive-date=2020-08-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200804175113/https://www.politico.com/news/2020/05/25/donald-trump-rigged-election-talk-fears-274477|dead-url=no}}</ref>，并称“若广泛使用邮寄选票将导致大规模的选举舞弊”。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Trump aides exploring executive actions to curb voting by mail|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2020/08/08/trump-wants-to-cut-mail-in-voting-the-republican-machine-is-helping-him-392428|accessdate=2020-12-14|last=Kumar|first=Anita|work=POLITICO|language=en|archive-date=2020-08-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200814174228/https://www.politico.com/news/2020/08/08/trump-wants-to-cut-mail-in-voting-the-republican-machine-is-helping-him-392428|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=Trump Is Pushing a False Argument on Vote-by-Mail Fraud. Here Are the Facts.|url=https://www.nytimes.com/article/mail-in-voting-explained.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2020-09-28|accessdate=2020-12-14|issn=0362-4331|language=en-US|first=Stephanie|last=Saul|first2=Reid J.|last2=Epstein|archive-date=2020-08-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200823115559/https://www.nytimes.com/article/mail-in-voting-explained.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>7月30日，特朗普提出推迟选举的想法，被《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》称之为“对总统礼教非同寻常的破坏”。<ref>{{Cite news|title=Trump Defends ‘Delay the Election’ Tweet, Even Though He Can’t Do It|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/07/30/us/elections/biden-vs-trump.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2020-07-30|accessdate=2020-12-14|issn=0362-4331|language=en-US|archive-date=2020-07-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200730121042/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/07/30/us/elections/biden-vs-trump.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>当8月众议院投票决定向美国邮政服务提供250亿美元的拨款，以提前应对预计会激增的邮寄选票时，特朗普否决了这笔拨款，称要阻止任何增加邮寄选票的行为。<ref>{{Cite news|title=Trump says Postal Service needs money for mail-in voting, but he’ll keep blocking funding|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/2020/08/12/postal-service-ballots-dejoy/|newspaper=Washington Post|accessdate=2020-12-14|issn=0190-8286|language=en-US|first=Jacob|last=Bogage|archive-date=2020-08-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200823151540/https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/2020/08/12/postal-service-ballots-dejoy/|dead-url=no}}</ref>2020年8月24日，美國[[共和黨全國代表大會|共和黨全國代表大會]]正式提名當勞·特朗普為[[共和黨_(美國)|共和黨]]在[[2020年美國總統選舉|2020年美國總統選舉]]的候選人。<ref>{{Cite news|title=美國共和黨正式提名特朗普競逐連任|url=https://news.now.com/home/international/player?newsId=403021|accessdate=2020-08-25|agency=Now新聞台|language=zh-hk|date=2020-08-25|archive-date=2020-08-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200828011322/https://news.now.com/home/international/player?newsId=403021|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=Nominating Trump, Republicans Rewrite His Record|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/08/24/us/politics/republican-convention-recap.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2020-08-24|accessdate=2020-12-14|issn=0362-4331|language=en-US|first=Jonathan|last=Martin|first2=Alexander|last2=Burns|first3=Annie|last3=Karni|archive-date=2020-08-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200824235019/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/08/24/us/politics/republican-convention-recap.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

因美國聯邦各州的投票機制和計票速度皆不一致，加上本次大選投票人口出現暴增，选举结果在11月3號投票日后的几天都無法正式獲得確認。而11月3号大选日结束后的凌晨2点，在計票结果尚不明确的情况下，特朗普即在白宫向支持者宣布自己已经胜選，并要求立即停止计票，称「...某些人企圖偷走这次的选举結果」。<ref>{{Cite news|title=With results from key states unclear, Trump declares victory|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/uk-usa-election-trump-statement-idUKKBN27K0U3|newspaper=Reuters|date=2020-11-04|accessdate=2020-12-14|language=en|first=Reuters|last=Staff|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103075040/https://www.reuters.com/article/uk-usa-election-trump-statement-idUKKBN27K0U3|dead-url=no}}</ref>然而几天過后計票結果逐漸明朗，拜登被部分媒体和学术机构预测为赢家<ref>{{Cite news|title=First CNN, then within minutes, most other news organizations called the race for Biden|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/media/2020/11/07/fox-news-biden-president/|newspaper=Washington Post|accessdate=2020-12-14|issn=0190-8286|language=en-US|first=Elahe|last=Izadi|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111114934/https://www.washingtonpost.com/media/2020/11/07/fox-news-biden-president/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="#2">{{Cite news|title=Presidential Election Results: Biden Wins|url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2020/11/03/us/elections/results-president.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2020-11-03|accessdate=2020-12-14|issn=0362-4331|language=en-US|archive-date=2020-12-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201210235246/https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2020/11/03/us/elections/results-president.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，面臨敗選的特朗普卻揚言「这次选举远未结束」，并在没有提供確切证据的情况下聲称选举舞弊。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Trump attorney Rudy Giuliani says Trump won't concede, revives baseless claims of voter fraud|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/elections/2020/11/07/joe-biden-victory-president-trump-claims-election-far-over/6202892002/|accessdate=2020-12-14|last=Fritze|first=Ledyard King and John|work=USA TODAY|language=en-US|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108054219/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/elections/2020/11/07/joe-biden-victory-president-trump-claims-election-far-over/6202892002/|dead-url=no}}</ref>特朗普竞选团队在至少5个州提起了16起不同的诉讼，隨後他在推特上發佈宣言，並说“我们会赢”。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://finance.ifeng.com/c/81IZ7BzgfLL|archive-url=http://www.freezepage.com/1605180455GKONZTBGOS|title=特朗普仍拒绝承认败选，并称“我们会赢”，拜登最新回应：真令人尴尬|publisher=凤凰网|archive-date=2020-11-12|accessdate=2020-11-12|dead-url=no}}</ref>法律专家表示，特朗普團隊所提起之诉讼几乎没有改变选举结果的可能。<ref>{{cite web|title=最后，审理川普选举诉讼的法官们都气笑了|url=http://news.ifeng.com/c/81KgSt3Nu6j|publisher=凤凰网|archive-url=http://www.freezepage.com/1605179611OBEDXTUFHM|archive-date=2020-11-12|accessdate=2020-11-12|dead-url=no}}</ref>特朗普同时阻止其政府官员与乔·拜登合作进行交接准备。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lamire|first1=Jonathan|title=Refusing to concede, Trump blocks cooperation on transition|url=https://apnews.com/article/joe-biden-donald-trump-virus-outbreak-elections-voting-fraud-and-irregularities-2d39186996f69de245e59c966d4d140f|work=[[AP_News|AP News]]|accessdate=November 10, 2020|date=November 10, 2020|archive-date=2020-11-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201110001227/https://apnews.com/article/joe-biden-donald-trump-virus-outbreak-elections-voting-fraud-and-irregularities-2d39186996f69de245e59c966d4d140f|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Timm|first1=Jane C.|last2=Smith|first2=Allan|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2020-election/trump-stonewalling-biden-s-transition-here-s-why-it-matters-n1247768|title=Trump is stonewalling Biden's transition. Here's why it matters.|work=[[NBC_News|NBC News]]|date=November 14, 2020|access-date=November 26, 2020|archive-date=2020-11-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125173748/https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2020-election/trump-stonewalling-biden-s-transition-here-s-why-it-matters-n1247768|dead-url=no}}</ref>11月16日，特朗普再次发推称自己赢得了大选，但被推特官方贴上标签“与官方消息源对这场选举判定的结果不同”。<ref>{{cite web|archive-url=http://www.freezepage.com/1605573871FFZCKOLTQR|publisher=环球网|archive-date=2020-11-17|title=特朗普再次发推说赢得了大选|url=https://world.huanqiu.com/article/40j83FAUGIM|accessdate=2020-11-17|dead-url=no}}</ref>到2020年11月底，特朗普或其盟友在[[搖擺州|摇摆州]]提出了50多起诉讼，但大部分被法院驳回。<ref name="#3">{{Cite web|title=Trump's election fight includes over 50 lawsuits. It's not going well.|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2020-election/trump-s-election-fight-includes-over-30-lawsuits-it-s-n1248289|accessdate=2020-12-14|work=NBC News|language=en|archive-date=2020-12-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201202071716/https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2020-election/trump-s-election-fight-includes-over-30-lawsuits-it-s-n1248289|dead-url=no}}</ref>12月5日，拜登在全国普选票数上以8130万张（51.3%）对7420万张（46.8%）领先特朗普。<ref name="#2"/><ref name="#4">{{Cite web|title=2020 US Presidential Election Results: Live Map|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Elections/2020-us-presidential-election-results-live-map/|accessdate=2020-12-14|last=News|first=A. B. C.|work=ABC News|language=en|archive-date=2021-01-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210110123555/https://abcnews.go.com/Elections/2020-us-presidential-election-results-live-map|dead-url=no}}</ref>预计拜登将以306票对232票赢得[[選舉人團_(美國)|選舉人團]]的选举<ref name="#4"/>

特朗普关于大范围投票舞弊的指控被法官、州选举官员和他自己的政府的{{Link-en|美国网络安全和基础设施安全局|Cybersecurity and Infrastructure Security Agency}}（CISA）局长驳斥。<ref name="conclusive">{{cite news|last1=Woodward|first1=Calvin|title=AP Fact Check: Trump conclusively lost, denies the evidence|url=https://apnews.com/article/ap-fact-check-trump-conclusively-lost-bbb9d8c808021ed65d91aee003a7bc64|accessdate=November 17, 2020|work=[[AP_News|AP News]]|date=November 17, 2020|archive-date=2020-11-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201117000041/https://apnews.com/article/ap-fact-check-trump-conclusively-lost-bbb9d8c808021ed65d91aee003a7bc64|dead-url=no}}</ref>在CISA局长克里斯托弗·克雷布斯（Christopher Krebs）反驳了特朗普的投票舞弊指控后，特朗普解雇了克雷布斯，称其对选举公正所作评论“非常不准确”。<ref>{{Cite web|title=特朗普解雇美国网络安全局长 指其选举言论“不准确”|url=https://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/simp/world-54983450|accessdate=2020-12-14|date=2020-11-18|work=BBC News 中文|language=zh-hans|archive-date=2020-11-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201127021625/https://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/simp/world-54983450|dead-url=no}}</ref>

由于大选后对选举结果的法律挑战基本失败<ref>{{cite news|work=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]|date=November 20, 2020|first=David|last=Smith|title=Trump makes futile last stand to overturn results as Georgia certifies Biden win|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/nov/20/trump-michigan-republicans-election|accessdate=2020-12-14|archive-date=2020-11-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201121060545/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/nov/20/trump-michigan-republicans-election|dead-url=no}}</ref>，特朗普淡出了公开活动，引来批评。有媒体认为他的退缩是不负责任的生闷气的表現尤其是在美国[[2019冠状病毒病疫情|冠状病毒病疫情]]激增的情况下。<ref>{{cite news|work=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]|date=November 21, 2020|first=David|last=Smith|title=Trump's monumental sulk: president retreats from public eye as Covid ravages US|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/nov/21/trump-monumental-sulk-president-retreats-from-public-eye-covid-ravages-us|accessdate=2020-12-14|archive-date=2021-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210111002105/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/nov/21/trump-monumental-sulk-president-retreats-from-public-eye-covid-ravages-us|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[联邦总务署|联邦总务署]]（GSA）局长埃米莉·墨菲（Emily Murphy）经过两周的抵抗后，宣布拜登看起来是选举的赢家，开始向拜登团队提供过渡资源。<ref>{{cite news|last=Rein|first=Lisa|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/gsa-emily-murphy-transition-biden/2020/11/23/c0f43e84-2de0-11eb-96c2-aac3f162215d_story.html|title=Under pressure, Trump appointee Emily Murphy approves transition in unusually personal letter to Biden|work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]]|date=November 24, 2020|access-date=November 24, 2020|archive-date=2020-11-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125212742/https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/gsa-emily-murphy-transition-biden/2020/11/23/c0f43e84-2de0-11eb-96c2-aac3f162215d_story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>11月23日，特朗普在推特上证实了“GSA局长当日致信拜登，表示将向后者提供大选后相应的资源和服务，玛丽·吉尔伯特（Mary Gilbert）也致信美国联邦政府各部门，称墨菲确定（ascertain）拜登和哈里斯是‘显然成功的候选人’”这一信息，并称是自己建议GSA开始过渡进程，但他仍坚称自己会“获胜”。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Naylor|first1=Brian|last2=Wise|first2=Alana|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/biden-transition-updates/2020/11/23/937956178/trump-administration-to-begin-biden-transition-protocols|title=Trump Is In No Mood To Concede, But Says Will Leave White House|work=[[NPR|NPR]]|date=November 23, 2020|access-date=December 11, 2020|archive-date=2020-12-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201211001656/https://www.npr.org/sections/biden-transition-updates/2020/11/23/937956178/trump-administration-to-begin-biden-transition-protocols|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=通知拜登开启权力过渡的GSA是什么机构？特朗普认输了吗？|url=http://news.ifeng.com/c/81enQUzXt1S|publisher=凤凰网|archive-url=http://www.freezepage.com/1606280460PUAGMNBSNN|archive-date=2020-11-25|accessdate=2020-11-25|dead-url=no}}</ref>

特朗普在11月26日表示，如果[[選舉人團_(美國)|選舉人團]]投票给当选总统拜登，他将离开白宫。<ref>{{Cite news|title=Trump Is In No Mood To Concede, But Says Will Leave White House|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/biden-transition-updates/2020/11/26/939386434/trump-is-in-no-mood-to-concede-but-says-will-leave-white-house|access-date=2020-12-04|website=[[NPR|NPR]]|date=November 26, 2020|first1=Franco|last1=Ordoñez|first2=Roberta|last2=Rampton|archive-date=2020-12-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201204030130/https://www.npr.org/sections/biden-transition-updates/2020/11/26/939386434/trump-is-in-no-mood-to-concede-but-says-will-leave-white-house|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=特朗普称如果选举人团投票给拜登 他将离开白宫|url=https://www.chinanews.com/gj/2020/11-27/9348540.shtml|publisher=中新网|archive-url=http://www.freezepage.com/1606437503OAZXZLZURF|archive-date=2020-11-27|accessdate=2020-11-27|dead-url=no}}</ref>但他及其盟友仍然努力地嘗試使本次選舉因“合法性問題”使之無效化。<ref name="#3"/>12月2日，特朗普指责在选举期间“发生了很多糟糕的事情”。他指控总统选举被操纵，充斥着欺诈行为。<ref>{{cite web|title=特朗普发表“可能是我最重要讲话”：如果我们是对的，拜登当不了总统！|url=https://world.huanqiu.com/article/40wuHPt5m8f|date=2020-12-03|publisher=环球网|archive-url=http://www.freezepage.com/1606981108ZMCYFTKWWV|archive-date=2020-12-03|accessdate=2020-12-03|dead-url=no}}</ref>2020年12月11日，美国最高法院拒绝审理由[[德克萨斯州|德克萨斯州]]总[[檢察官|檢察长]]提起的、得到特朗普及其共和党盟友支持的案件。原告曾要求法院推翻拜登赢得的四个州的选举结果。<ref name="auto5">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/12/11/us/politics/supreme-court-election-texas.html|title=Supreme Court Rejects Texas Suit Seeking to Subvert Election|first=Adam|last=Liptak|authorlink=Adam Liptak|date=December 11, 2020|work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|accessdate=2020-12-14|archive-date=2020-12-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201211234955/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/12/11/us/politics/supreme-court-election-texas.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>12月14日，选举人团以306-232票正式确定拜登获胜。<ref>{{cite news |work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]] |date=December 14, 2020 |first1=Josh |last1=Holder |first2=Trip |last2=Gabriel |author2link=Trip Gabriel |first3=Isabella Grullón |last3=Paz |title=Biden's 306 Electoral College Votes Make His Victory Official |url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2020/12/14/us/elections/electoral-college-results.html |accessdate=2020-12-17 |archive-date=2021-01-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107151640/https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2020/12/14/us/elections/electoral-college-results.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>2021年1月7日，发布声明称不同意选举结果，不过在1月20日将“有序”交接权力<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/nation/2021/01/07/trump-promises-orderly-transition/|title=Trump promises ‘orderly transition’ to Biden administration, one day after inciting mob to storm Capitol|publisher=The Washington Post|accessdate=2021-01-08|archive-date=2021-01-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107222110/https://www.washingtonpost.com/nation/2021/01/07/trump-promises-orderly-transition/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.ifeng.com/c/82qS5lo6HAl|title=“拜登赢了”，特朗普承诺“有序”交接，网友打了个颇具讽刺意味的比喻……|publisher=凤凰网|archive-url=http://www.freezepage.com/1610083127XHQLDWAXDB|archive-date=2021-01-08|dead-url=no|accessdate=2021-01-08}}</ref>。

== 卸任后 ==
===總統尾聲===
自2020年11月3日至2021年1月19日，特朗普政府的[[美国财政部|美国财政部]][[外国资产管制办公室|外国资产管制办公室]]宣布了307项个人和实体黑名单认定。在此期間特朗普政府颁布的制裁数量高于前几届政府，也比他任期的其他時期更多，特朗普任期内平均每年约有1,000个实体和个人被列入黑名单<ref>{{cite news |title=去年选举日迄今特朗普政府颁布的制裁数量高于前几届政府 |url=https://cn.wsj.com/articles/%E5%8E%BB%E5%B9%B4%E9%80%89%E4%B8%BE%E6%97%A5%E8%BF%84%E4%BB%8A%E7%89%B9%E6%9C%97%E6%99%AE%E6%94%BF%E5%BA%9C%E9%A2%81%E5%B8%83%E7%9A%84%E5%88%B6%E8%A3%81%E6%95%B0%E9%87%8F%E9%AB%98%E4%BA%8E%E5%89%8D%E5%87%A0%E5%B1%8A%E6%94%BF%E5%BA%9C-11611201011 |accessdate=2021-01-21 |archive-date=2021-01-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210121115540/https://cn.wsj.com/articles/%E5%8E%BB%E5%B9%B4%E9%80%89%E4%B8%BE%E6%97%A5%E8%BF%84%E4%BB%8A%E7%89%B9%E6%9C%97%E6%99%AE%E6%94%BF%E5%BA%9C%E9%A2%81%E5%B8%83%E7%9A%84%E5%88%B6%E8%A3%81%E6%95%B0%E9%87%8F%E9%AB%98%E4%BA%8E%E5%89%8D%E5%87%A0%E5%B1%8A%E6%94%BF%E5%BA%9C-11611201011 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2021年1月20日8时15分，特朗普與妻子梅拉尼娅搭乘[[海军陆战队一号|海军陆战队一号]]离开白宫，前往[[安德鲁斯空军基地|安德鲁斯空军基地]]參加简短告别仪式。特朗普拒絕出席數小時後舉辦的[[2021年美國總統就職典禮|拜登總統就職典禮]]<ref>{{cite news |title=从“美国优先”到“美国孤独”，特朗普时代落幕 |url=http://www.chinanews.com/gj/2021/01-20/9392475.shtml |accessdate=2021-01-21 |archive-date=2021-01-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210124170050/http://www.chinanews.com/gj/2021/01-20/9392475.shtml |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

